data.title: Sagrada Familia in Barcelona reaches 162.91 meters with placement of lower arm on Tower of Jesus Christ.
data.description: In Barcelona, Spain, as of October 31, 2025, an important milestone has been achieved in the construction of the Basílica de la Sagrada Família. The Tower of Jesus Christ now stands at a height of 162.91 meters after the placement of the lower arm. This marks a significant step forward in the completion of this iconic structure that has been in progress for many years.

data.title: Newell Brands (NASDAQ: NWL) reports Q3 2025 financial results despite trade disruptions. CEO states sales were affected.
data.description: In Atlanta, Newell Brands (NASDAQ: NWL) revealed its financial results for the third quarter of 2025. Chris Peterson, President and CEO of Newell Brands, emphasized the progress of their turnaround despite facing trade disruptions during the quarter. The company quickly implemented strategic measures such as sourcing alterations, pricing adjustments, and productivity enhancements to counter the challenges. Sales figures were impacted by these disruptions.

data.title: Kuick Research predicts global multispecific antibody market to surpass USD 50 billion by 2030 with sales over USD 12 billion in 2024. 700+ antibodies in clinical trials show exciting M&A opportunities. More info at: https://www.kuickresearch.com/report-multispecific-antibodies-market
data.description: Kuick Research has released a Global Multispecific Antibodies Market Report aimed at investors and corporate development teams, highlighting the potential of this rapidly advancing biotechnology sector. The report provides insights on the market opportunity, with projections of over USD 50 billion by 2030 and sales exceeding USD 12 billion in 2024. Currently, there are 18 approved multispecific antibodies, with over 700 in various stages of clinical trials worldwide. These antibodies are revolutionizing therapeutic strategies in oncology, hematology, and autoimmune diseases, attracting investment opportunities for both established pharmaceutical companies and emerging biotech firms. The full story is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Empowering children with disabilities in Central African Republic to access inclusive education by Education Cannot Wait, UNICEF, and partners.
data.description: In the region of Bambari in the Central African Republic, Education Cannot Wait, along with UNICEF and their collaborators, are working towards providing children with disabilities the opportunity to receive inclusive education and achieve their maximum capabilities. Taking place in the town of Bambari, the project aims to improve educational access for these children. The initiative, launched on October 31, 2025, is crucial for empowering children in the area.
